    "output": "{\"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"status_reasoning\\\": {\\n    \\\"determined_status\\\": \\\"degraded\\\",\\n    \\\"status_justification\\\": [\\n      \\\"All 16 pods in namespace sock-shop are in Running phase and Ready, with no CrashLoopBackOff or Pending pods.\\\",\\n      \\\"Events show transient startup probe failures for carts but no ongoing Unhealthy events.\\\",\\n      \\\"flash-agent pod (2/2 containers, recent restarts) and its image/labels indicate an injected disturbance/chaos-style agent operating in the namespace.\\\",\\n      \\\"Resource metrics via metrics.k8s.io are forbidden for this service account, so live utilization cannot be validated.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"data_quality\\\": {\\n      \\\"completeness\\\": \\\"partial\\\",\\n      \\\"gaps\\\": [\\n        \\\"metrics_unavailable\\\",\\n        \\\"events_truncated\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"confidence_impact\\\": \\\"Health score slightly reduced due to missing resource metrics and truncated event history, but pod and event data are sufficient for a reasonable assessment.\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"thoughts\\\": {\\n    \\\"key_observations\\\": [\\n      \\\"Namespace sock-shop currently has 16 pods, all in Running status and Ready.\\\",\\n      \\\"Core sock-shop microservices (carts, catalogue, orders, payment, shipping, user, their DBs, queue-master, rabbitmq, front-end) are all present and healthy.\\\",\\n      \\\"A flash-agent pod (app=flash-agent) is running with 2 containers and has recorded 2 restarts recently, which is atypical compared to the rest of the fleet.\\\",\\n      \\\"Events show normal scheduling, image pull, container creation, and start messages for all pods.\\\",\\n      \\\"carts pod experienced startup probe failures (connection refused and timeout) early in its lifecycle but has since recovered.\\\",\\n      \\\"No events contain explicit chaos/fault/inject/disrupt keywords, but the presence and naming of flash-agent strongly suggest an external dis